<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-245-334  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 245 334.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  March 1990 v27 n3 p49(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Select the right hardware: a good interconnection strategy takestime and study. (tutorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hawkins, Paul D.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A tutorial on integrating fiber optics into premises communicationwiring is presented.andP;  Before fiber-optic hardware can bespecified, cable fiber count and routing design must bedetermined.andP;  Interconnection hardware should accept differenttypes of cables and splices and should be universally compatiblewith OEM computer systems.andP;  Upgradeability is a primaryconsideration.andP;  Outside plant hardware must be able to tolerateadverse environmental conditions.andP;  Indoor hardware should beselected on the basis of termination method, mounting location,and fiber count, which must allow for future expansion.andP;  Wiringclosets should facilitate system rearrangement by ensuring easyaccess to connectors, strain relief and retaining guides should beprovided, and system security can be ensured by the use of alockable hasp.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TutorialFiber opticsOn-SiteHardware Selection.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>